    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7350" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πείθω</span></b> , ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔπειθον, πεῖθε</span>, fut. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεισέμεν</span>, aor. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεῖσαι</span>, aor. 2 red. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέπιθον</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεπιθήσω</span>,
          mid. opt. 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πειθοίατο</span>, ipf.
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πείθετο</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πείσομαι</span>,
          aor. 2 (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πιθόμην</span>, red. opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεπίθοιτο</span>, perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέποιθα</span>,
          subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεποίθω</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεποίθει</span>, 1 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπέπιθμεν</span>: I. act., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">make to believe, convince,
            persuade, prevail</span>
          
          <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">upon</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινά, φρένας
            τινός</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, and w.
          inf.; the persuasion may be for better or for worse, ‘talk over,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 1.132</span></i>; ‘mollify,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 1.100</span></i>.—II. (1) mid., allow oneself to
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be prevailed upon, obey, mind;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μύ̄θῳ, τινὶ μύ̄θοις,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 23.157</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            τεράεσσι,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 4.408</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἅ
            τιν᾽ οὐ πείσεσθαι ὀί̄ω</span>, ‘wherein methinks many a one will
          not comply,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 1.289</span></i>.—(2) perf.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πέποιθα</span> and plup., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">put trust
            in, depend upon;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί, ἀλκί</span>, etc., <i><span class="en">Od. 10.335</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            16.98</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
